<TITLE> Cold wave sweeps at night </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 1 (bdnews24.com)  A mild cold wave is sweeping through the country on Friday night, Bangladesh Meteorological Department said Friday. People in Dhaka, Rajshahi and Khulna divisions and the regions of Srimangal and Comilla are expected to experience severe cold. Moderate to thick fog may exist over the northwestern part of the country and a blanket of light to moderate may occur elsewhere over the country during midnight till morning. Met office forecast officer Abdur Rahman Khan old bdnews24.com, "The cold wave may sweep over some regions of the country. The night temperature may fall slightly to 8-10 degree Celsius." Rahman said the highest temperature in Dhaka on Friday was recorded at 23 degree Celsius while the lowest temperature was 13.08 degree Celsius. A mild cold wave has been sweeping over Chuadanga and Jessore since last Thursday. bdne
